<TITLE> Suspected extremist 'killed by rival group' </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Pabna, Apr 25 (bdnews24.com)  A leader of the outlawed extremist outfit Purbo Bangla Communist Party (ML-Red Flag) was killed in Pabna, possibly by a rival group, said police on Saturday. The dead man was identified by police as 'Alam', son of Khorshed Ali of Shibpur village in Atghoria Upazila. Some 10-12 unidentified men took Alam from his home on Friday evening, stabbed him and left him for dead, Atghoria police chief Sirajul Islam told bdnews24.com. "The assailants may have been members of a rival extremist group," said the police officer. Alam was taken to Rajshahi Medical College Hospital in critical condition where he died in the night, said Islam. A case was filed with Atghoria Police Station. Nobody had been arrested upto Saturday morning, said Islam. bdnews
